cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.MM. 

This paper is about evaluating single-object tracking algorithms using a new long-term, large-scale tracking dataset. The dataset is designed to be more representative of real-world scenarios, where targets may disappear and sequences may be longer than a few seconds. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is computer vision (cs.CV), followed by artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Robotics (cs.RO) and multimedia (cs.MM) are also possible sub-categories, as they may involve tracking objects in real-world environments and analyzing video data.
